      <p>
        This project is part of the CS 461 Senior Capstone at Oregon State University.
        Version 2 builds upon the original Interactive Survey Tool for Data Visualization,
        continuing its development as a web-based survey platform that enables researchers
        to create interactive, data-driven questionnaires with dynamic visualizations for
        richer and more precise participant insights.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Project Overview -->
    <section class="about-section">
      <h3>Project Overview</h3>
      <p>
        The goal of this project is to develop a custom web-based survey tool that allows
        researchers at Oregon State University (and other organizations) to create
        interactive surveys featuring advanced data visualizations. Unlike existing
        platforms such as Qualtrics, this tool supports dynamic elements including
        zooming, panning, and selecting regions on visual assets such as SVGs.
      </p>
      <p>
        By enabling these interactive features, the platform helps researchers collect
        more nuanced and insightful data. The project emphasizes usability, accessibility,
        and data security, aiming to enhance both the researcher and participant experience
        while addressing limitations of current survey tools.
      </p>
    </section>

